One person  died and two others were  wounded when a gunman opened fire on a group of people at a tavern in the Eastern Cape, police said on Monday. Police spokesperson Capt Gerda Swart said the  man entered the tavern in KwaNobuhle, on the outskirts of Uitenhage, in the early hours of Sunday morning. After opening fire on the group, the man fled the scene and community members alerted police, Swart said. A 27-year-old man, who sustained multiple gunshot wounds, was declared dead on the scene. Two others were  treated for injuries to  their legs and arms. The motive for the shooting was unknown. Cases of murder and attempted murder are being investigated.